def create_gabor_grid(frequencies, widths, samples_per_period):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(widths), len(frequencies), figsize=(15, 12))

    fixed_t_range = np.linspace(-3 * (1 / frequencies[0]), 3 * (1 / frequencies[0]), 10000)

    for i, n in enumerate(widths):
        for j, f in enumerate(frequencies):
            sigma = n / f
            fs = f * samples_per_period
            t = fixed_t_range  

            gabor_function = gabor(t, sigma, f)

            ax = axes[i, j]
            ax.plot(t, gabor_function, label=f"f={f} Hz, σ={sigma:.3f}, n={n}")
            ax.set_title(f"f={f} Hz, σ={sigma:.3f}, n={n}")
            ax.set_xlabel("Time (s)")
            ax.set_ylabel("Amplitude")
            ax.legend()
            ax.grid(True)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


frequencies = [100, 200, 300] 
width_factors = [1, 2, 3]  
samples_per_period = 16  

create_gabor_grid(frequencies, width_factors, samples_per_period)

In [18]:
fs = 200  
f = 5     
t = np.arange(0, 0.5, 1/fs)  

# Generate sine wave
sine_wave = np.sin(2 * np.pi * f * t)

# Define threshold
threshold = 0.5

# Function to find threshold crossings
def crossings(signal, threshold, dir="both"):
    signal = np.asarray(signal)
    crossings = []
    if dir == "negpos":
        crossings = np.where((signal[:-1] < threshold) & (signal[1:] >= threshold))[0] + 1
    elif dir == "posneg":
        crossings = np.where((signal[:-1] >= threshold) & (signal[1:] < threshold))[0] + 1
    elif dir == "both":
        negpos_crossings = np.where((signal[:-1] < threshold) & (signal[1:] >= threshold))[0] + 1
        posneg_crossings = np.where((signal[:-1] >= threshold) & (signal[1:] < threshold))[0] + 1
        crossings = np.sort(np.concatenate((negpos_crossings, posneg_crossings)))
    return crossings

# Find crossing indices
crossing_indices = crossings(sine_wave, threshold)

# Plot the sine wave
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(t, sine_wave, label="5 Hz Sine Wave")
plt.axhline(y=threshold, color='r', linestyle='--', label="Threshold (0.5)")
plt.scatter(t[crossing_indices], sine_wave[crossing_indices], color='black', zorder=3, label="Crossings")

# Labels and title
plt.xlabel("Time (s)")
plt.ylabel("Amplitude")
plt.title("5 Hz Sine Wave with Threshold Crossings")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Load the WAV file
fs, data = wavfile.read("speech.wav")  # Ensure "speech.wav" is in the same folder

# Convert to mono if stereo
if len(data.shape) > 1:
    data = np.mean(data, axis=1)  # Convert stereo to mono

# Define time range
start_time = 3.0  # Start at 3.0 seconds
end_time = 3.1    # End at 3.1 seconds

# Convert time to sample index
start_sample = int(start_time * fs)
end_sample = int(end_time * fs)

# Extract the waveform segment
time_segment = np.linspace(start_time, end_time, end_sample - start_sample)
audio_segment = data[start_sample:end_sample]

# Plot the waveform
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
plt.plot(time_segment, audio_segment, label="Audio Waveform")
plt.xlabel("Time (s)")
plt.ylabel("Amplitude")
plt.title("Waveform of 'speech.wav' from 3.0 to 3.1 seconds")
plt.legend()
plt.grid()
plt.show()

# Load audio file
samplerate, data = wavfile.read("speech.wav")

# Convert to mono if stereo
if len(data.shape) > 1:
    data = data.mean(axis=1)  # Average the two channels

# Compute envelope
ylower, yupper, blockindices = envelope(data, nblocks=500)

time = np.linspace(0, len(data) / samplerate, len(data))
block_time = time[blockindices]

# Plot waveform with envelope
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(time, data, alpha=0.5, label='Waveform')
plt.plot(block_time, ylower, 'r', label='Lower Envelope')
plt.plot(block_time, yupper, 'g', label='Upper Envelope')
plt.xlabel('Time (seconds)')
plt.ylabel('Amplitude')
plt.title('Audio Envelope of speech.wav')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
